.Ve
.PP
Returns the number of inputs the PSBT defines.
.PP
\fIoutput_count\fR
.IX Subsection "output_count"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $int = $object\->output_count()
.Ve
.PP
Returns the number of outputs the PSBT defines.
.PP
\fIget_field\fR
.IX Subsection "get_field"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $field = $object\->get_field($field_type_name, $map_index = undef, $key = undef)
.Ve
.PP
Tries to get a field of \f(CW$field_type_name\fR as defined in BIP174, for example
\&\f(CW\*(C`PSBT_GLOBAL_UNSIGNED_TX\*(C'\fR. If the field is from input or output maps, it also
requires \f(CW$map_index\fR to be passed (0\-based index of the input or output).
Optional \f(CW$key\fR (a bytestring) can be provided if this PSBT field defines keys.
.PP
Returns an instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::Field, which you can use to
access key and value data.
.PP
If there isn\*(Aqt exactly one field with this type in the map, it will throw an
exception. This allows you to write the following without checking the return
value of the function:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        my $output_index_0 = $object\->get_field(\*(AqPSBT_IN_OUTPUT_INDEX\*(Aq, 0)\->value;
.Ve
.PP
See "get_all_fields" for a variant which does not check the field count.
.PP
\fIget_all_fields\fR
.IX Subsection "get_all_fields"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        @fields = $object\->get_all_fields($field_type_name, $map_index = undef, $key = undef)
.Ve
.PP
Same as "get_field", but will return all the fields of given type from a
given map. It may be used if the field exists, or to get multiple fields with
different key data.
.PP
The return value is a list (not an array), so using it in scalar context will
get the last found field (as opposed to a field count).
.PP
\fIadd_field\fR
.IX Subsection "add_field"
.PP
.Vb 2
\&        $object = $object\->add_field(%field_data)
\&        $object = $object\->add_field($field_object, $map_index = undef)
.Ve
.PP
Adds a new field to the PSBT. It can be run either with \f(CW%field_data\fR (a hash
arguments for the "new" in Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::Field) or with \f(CW$field_object\fR
(constructed Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::Field) and \f(CW$map_index\fR.
.PP
If passing \f(CW%field_data\fR hash, it can contain an additional \f(CW\*(C`index\*(C'\fR key to
represent \f(CW$map_index\fR. The field will be constructed and added to the map.
Adding the index to a map triggers its validations, so it must be complete
enough to pass them. For this reason, sometimes it could be more preferable to
construct and fill the field by hand before adding it to the PSBT.
.PP
Note that a field cannot be used in more than one map at a time.
.PP
\fIlist_fields\fR
.IX Subsection "list_fields"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        @list = $object\->list_fields()
.Ve
.PP
This method lists all fields present in the PSBT. It returns a list of array
references, each array reference has two elements: field type and map index.
These are the same elements that are needed in "get_all_fields" calls, so you
may use this data to loop through PSBT fields.
.PP
\fIcheck\fR
.IX Subsection "check"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $object = $object\->check()
.Ve
.PP
Checks the internal state of PSBT fields and throws an exception if it is
invalid. Returns the object itself.
.PP
\fIto_serialized\fR
.IX Subsection "to_serialized"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $serialized = $object\->to_serialized()
.Ve
.PP
Serializes a PSBT into a bytestring. "check" is called automatically before
serializing.
.PP
\fIfrom_serialized\fR
.IX Subsection "from_serialized"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $object = $class\->from_serialized($data)
.Ve
.PP
Deserializes the bytestring \f(CW$data\fR into a PSBT object. "check" is called
automatically after deserializing.
.PP
\fIdump\fR
.IX Subsection "dump"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $text = $object\->dump()
.Ve
.PP
Returns a readable description of all the maps in the PSBT.
.SH "FIELD REFERENCE"
.IX Header "FIELD REFERENCE"
Just for reference, here is a list of all PSBT fields which are currently
supported by this module. This list is auto\-generated from
"key_data" in Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::FieldType and
"value_data" in Bitcoin::Crypto::PSBT::FieldType (which contain short strings
with description of field content).
.PP
For a list of PSBT fields, see
BIP174 <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0174.mediawiki>.
